{"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-30gyb","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-5ndjt","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-6lhvr","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-7apmz","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(_:)-8rbuv","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(raw:)-1nyk4","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(raw:)-5it8v","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retainingRaw:)-290rd","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/init(retainingRaw:)-8drmn"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/ptr"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex\/StaticMutexProtocol-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" works like a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticmutex"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutex"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":" can be statically allocated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is a version of our ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"give_me_next_number()"},{"type":"text","text":" example using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a GStaticMutex:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"want to require prior calling to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", because your code"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" and thus "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":", as that requires a prior call to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". In these cases you can also use a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It must be initialized with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and freed with with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_free()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when not needed anymore to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free up any allocated resources."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Even though ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()"},{"text":" can also be used even if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which does nothing but returning "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text",